==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Corydalus
<hw>Corydalus</hw> <pos>prop. n.</pos> <def>The type genus of the
<fam>Corydalidae</fam>. It includes the dobsonfly (<spn>Corydalus
cornutus</spn>), whose aquatic larva, the <stype>hellgrammite</stype>,
is used as bait in fishing.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> genus <gen>Corydalus</gen>, genus
Corydalis.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Corylaceae</ent>⟦br⟧
